HEADWORD: Heptylene
<hw>Hep"tyl*ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless liquid hydrocarbon, <chform>C7H14</chform>, of the
ethylene series; also, any one of its isomers. Called also
<altname>heptene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heptylic</ent>⟦br⟧
